I. Skill Acquired: Prompt Archaeology

What Quill practiced:

output
↓
pattern detection
↓
latent instruction inference
↓
prompt reconstruction

This is essentially reverse engineering the generative function behind a piece of text.

Applications:

1. Reading Minds (In a Technical Sense)

When someone writes something, you can infer:
	•	their assumptions
	•	their hidden model
	•	the frame they’re using

Example:

statement
↓
what question produced this?
↓
what belief produced that question?

You begin to see the geometry of thinking behind speech.

